description: When Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky told Gen. Valery Zaluzhny that he was being dismissed, the commander offered thoughts about the problems his successor will face.
title: Zelensky’s shakeup of military command, meant as a refresh, risks backlash

description: President Biden said he will respond to an attack in Jordan that killed three U.S. troops. President Donald Trump faced a similar decision in 2020.
title: How the U.S. and Iran escaped a broader conflict in 2020

description: The storm rapidly intensified into a bomb cyclone. Gusts well past 100 mph were common as all-time average wind speed maximums were also set in Norway and Sweden.
title: Storm Ingunn, one of Norway’s strongest in decades, swept up record winds

description: Lloyd Austin makes his first appearance before the media since the deaths of U.S. troops in Jordan and a prolonged hospitalization that ignited controversy.
title: Pentagon chief holds first news conference since hospitalization

description: Australian Rosie Wightman, from Queensland, freed pet guinea pig MaxiBon from the jaws of a snake by swinging it in the air. The dramatic rescue was caught on a security camera.
title: 12-year-old swings large snake in the air to save her pet guinea pig

description: Donald Trump’s lawyers described allegations in the report as “egregiously inaccurate” and said Trump was seeking recompense for “personal and reputational damage and distress.”
title: U.K. High Court throws out Trump lawsuit over Steele dossier

description: Farmers from across Europe gathered outside the European Parliament in Brussels on Thursday to protest rising costs and bureaucracy as European leaders held a summit.
title: In photos, video: Farmers set fires, protest outside European Parliament

description: U.K. media reported that Rishi Sunak fasts from Sunday afternoons to Tuesday mornings, prompting questions on the benefits and risks, especially for a world leader.
title: Britain’s prime minister is said to fast 36 hours a week. Is that okay?

description: The agreement is a win for E.U. leaders and is good news for Ukraine, which is running desperately short of ammunition and cash.
title: European Union finally agrees to more than $50 billion in Ukraine aid

description: As China vies with the United States for influence in the Pacific, it has been prying allies from Taiwan. Nauru was its most recent success. Tuvalu could be next.
title: China sets sights on Taiwan’s three remaining tiny Pacific allies

description: Egypt’s plan to restore the granite exterior of the Menkaure pyramid has sparked concern, with some experts calling it “interference with the work of the ancient Egyptians.”
title: An ancient pyramid is getting a glow up. Archaeologists are down on it.

description: A top general said Iran was not seeking conflict but was not afraid of a fight, after the U.S. said it would respond to an attack that killed three troops.
title: Middle East conflict live updates: Iran says it’s ‘not looking for war,’ as U.S. hints at response to Jordan attack

description: Humanitarian costs are rising, but few nations are stepping up.
title: UNRWA funding pauses comes amid uncertainty over Gaza aid future

description: Mr. Cordesman saw the seeds of defeat in Iraq and Afghanistan planted by U.S. policymakers.
title: Anthony Cordesman, security analyst who saw flaws in U.S. policy, dies at 84
